In this release we have made Tweek even more convenient for those using the free version! Tweek now runs faster with the new Hermes engine Dark mode and task notes are now available to all users Removed restrictions on inviting users to your calendar Fixed an issue with syncing with Google Calendar Search now indexes all calendars Other minor bugs and fixes. Plus follow updates on Twitter tweekHQ.

New features and fixes Monthly view now available! Fixed duplication of events retrieved from Google Calendar. Fixed time zone bug. New task focus improvements. Other minor bugs and fixes. Follow tweekHQ on Twitter for more updates.

This release focuses on improving integration with calendars bugs with task sorting and fixes for recurring events. The Go to Today feature has undergone some adjustments to make it work better. Please check tweekHQ on Twitter for the latest information.

New features and fixes You can now choose to drop or leave completed tasks in your calendar settings. Improved task sorting. Fixed an issue where the title of Someday was not saved on the mobile app. We will continue to provide you with the latest information on Twitter tweekHQ.

New features and fixes Tasks are now auto saved as you type. Improved Google Calendar sorting function to display events in chronological order Invited users now inherit premium features from the calendar owner Haptic effects can now be turned off if desired Widget improvements Other minor bugs and fixes Please check tweekHQ on Twitter for the latest information.

New features and fixes. Updated repetitive tasks! You can now add notes or edit a single task without changing the entire cycle Fixed duplicate events retrieved from Google Calendar Widget improvements Other minor bugs and fixes Please check tweekHQ on Twitter for the latest information.
New features and fixes Compact calendar display with small fonts and margins Collapse and expand Someday list Other minor bugs and fixes Stay tuned for more updates on Twitter tweekHQ.

Introducing Tweek 2.0 a completely revamped ultra fast app with improved performance and support for offline mode. We have made some changes to the UI to provide the best user experience. I look forward to working with you. Follow us on Twitter tweekHQ for the latest updates.

Introducing Tweek 2.0 a completely revamped app with improved performance and offline mode support. We slightly redesigned the UI to provide you with best usage experience. More to come! Follow us on Twitter tweekHQ for updates.
Bug fixes Improvements
bug fixes offline mode enhancement.

Push notifications Reminders are now being sent through native push notifications. Multi language support Tweek is now available in Spanish Portuguese German Russian Italian and Chinese. It s been a long and quite hard journey but it would have been even tougher without the support of our community.

Introducing Home Screen widgets Now you can set up small or mid size Tweek widgets on your Home screen. Tasks Notes and Checklists Feel free to add rich text task notes and checklists. You can use the notes feature to add whatever is required for a particular task. Fixed the appearance of a white screen after clicking the Continue with Apple Continue with Google buttons. We are constantly improving Tweek. This update also includes minor fixes and performance upgrades.
